    "## MONDAY — print() and Comments\n",
    "\n",
    "`print()` is a function: a reusable action Python knows how to perform. It takes whatever is inside its parentheses and displays it on screen. Run each cell with **Shift + Enter**.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ed920627",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example 1 — Printing plain text\n",
    "Read the code, then run it. Confirm the three lines appear."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "588f8983",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# A comment — Python ignores everything after the # symbol\n",
    "# Use comments to explain what your code is doing and why\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"The Golden Fork Restaurant\")     # displays a string (text in quotes)\n",
    "print(\"Daily Revenue Calculator\")\n",
    "print(\"By: Zara Okonkwo, Meridian Consulting\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aba71a85",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example 2 — Single vs double quotes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ad526b92",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Both single and double quotes create strings — choose one and be consistent\n",
    "print(\"Jollof Rice\")       # double quotes\n",
    "print('Pounded Yam')      # single quotes — equally valid\n",
    "print(\"Today's Special\")  # use double quotes when text contains an apostrophe\n",
    "print('She said \"hello\"') # use single quotes when text contains double quotes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "60c18105",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example 3 — Printing numbers (no quotes needed)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "5e097552",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Numbers do not need quotes — Python recognises them directly\n",
    "print(1800)       # integer (whole number)\n",
    "print(3.14)       # float (decimal)\n",
    "print(98500)      # large integer\n",
    "\n",
    "# KEY RULE: \"1800\" (with quotes) is TEXT. 1800 (no quotes) is a NUMBER.\n",
    "# They look the same on screen but behave differently — you will see this on Tuesday."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e738ea0b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example 4 — Multiple items in one print()"
   ]
